Despite the intensity of my emotions in that moment, I immediately realized the gravity of my actions and promptly took my employee to the closest emergency room. I recognize the pain and distress I caused him and take full responsibility for my behavior. I extend my sincerest apologies to the victim and his family for the harm I inflicted upon him.

In an effort to demonstrate my genuine remorse, I have already committed to covering the remaining expenses of his hospital bills. I am deeply remorseful for the pain and suffering I caused him and acknowledge the impact it has had on his life.

Prior to this incident, I have maintained a clean record and have upheld the law as a responsible member of society. While I deeply regret my actions on that day, I understand that they do not reflect my true character. I am dedicated to learning from this experience and ensuring that it never happens again.

By entering this guilty plea, I willingly accept the consequences of my actions. I humbly request that the court consider this as a mitigating factor during the sentencing process. My aim is not to evade responsibility, but to show that I recognize the severity of my wrongdoing and commit to making amends.

I implore the court to take into account the specific circumstances of this case, along with my guilty plea, when determining an appropriate sentence. I am prepared to face the consequences of my actions and am committed to personal growth and rehabilitation moving forward.

I would like to express my gratitude to Your Honor for the time and consideration given to my plea. Thank you for giving me the opportunity to address the court, and I assure you that I am sincere in my remorse and my willingness to change and make things right.

Thank you.
