Your Honor,

I come before this esteemed court today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I, Aleksander Nowak, fully acknowledge my responsibility for the regrettable incident involving my employee. I pushed him to the ground and kicked him in the stomach, actions that were fueled by my extreme anger stemming from his significant mistake at work.

I am deeply remorseful for my actions and understand the gravity of the harm I caused. Immediately after the incident, I rushed my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure he received the necessary medical attention. I take full ownership of my actions and sincerely apologize to the victim and his family for the pain and distress I have caused them.

To demonstrate my genuine remorse, I have already offered to cover the remaining expenses of my employee's hospital bills. It is crucial to me that he receives the care and support needed during his recovery.

At 40 years old, I have no prior criminal record, which I believe speaks to the fact that this incident is an aberration in my behavior. The incident has served as a wake-up call for me, leading me to reflect on my actions and commit to personal growth and improvement.

I humbly implore the court to consider my sincere regret and willingness to make amends when determining my sentence. I am fully prepared to accept the consequences of my actions and dedicate myself to becoming a better person.

Thank you for your consideration.
NEW STATEMENT:

977
Your Honor,

I stand before this honorable court today, fully acknowledging my responsibility for the regrettable incident involving my employee. As Aleksander Nowak, I humbly plead guilty to the charge of assault, understanding the gravity of my actions.

I deeply regret my undeniable role in pushing my employee to the ground and subsequently kicking him in the stomach. These actions were inexcusable and were fueled by my extreme anger, which was a direct result of his significant mistake at work. However, it is crucial for the court to know that this behavior is completely out of character for me.

I want to emphasize that immediately after the incident, I recognized the severity of my actions and rushed my employee to the nearest emergency room. It was essential for me to ensure that he received the necessary medical attention to alleviate any harm caused. I take full ownership of my reprehensible behavior, and I sincerely apologize to the victim and his family for the pain and distress I have inflicted upon them.

To demonstrate my genuine remorse, I have offered to cover the remaining expenses of my employee's hospital bills. It is of utmost importance to me that he receives the care and support needed during his recovery process. I am committed to making amends and providing whatever assistance is necessary to help him move forward.

At 40 years old, I have no prior criminal record, which speaks to the fact that this incident is an isolated aberration in my otherwise law-abiding life. The incident has served as a profound wake-up call, prompting me to deeply reflect on my actions and commit to personal growth and improvement. I assure the court that this incident has forever changed me, and I am determined to become a better person because of it.

In light of my sincere regret and my unwavering dedication to making amends, I respectfully implore the court to consider these factors when determining my sentence. I am prepared to fully accept the consequences of my actions and demonstrate through my future behavior the true extent of my remorse.

Thank you for your understanding and consideration.

Sincerely,
Aleksander Nowak
